snp / chatsnoop               Asks to start/stop snooping on chat contacts
 
   Format:
      ;snp -n <name>          Makes request to chat contacts called <name>
      ;snp -g <group>         Makes request to chat contacts in the <group>
      ;snp                    Makes request to everyone
 
   Notes:
      The Chat task is used to chat with other players directly via telnet.
         Calls can be placed (or accepted) with any user whose MUD client uses
         the zChat or MudMaster protocols.
      This command is the equivalent of typing ';snoop' in the relevant Chat
         task windows.
      The switches -n and -g can't be combined.
 
   User commands:
      snp / snoop / chatsnoop
